<br>
Heres what happened:<br>
Climb wall with friends,<br>
Pick target<br>
Attack <br>
AOE Mezzed<br>
Dead<br>
<br>
Dead right at the area where u climb in.<br>
<br>
Guess Ill not be doing that any more.<br>
<br>
<br>
Shivian Slingblade<br>
46 Shaddowblade Galahad <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#3B3B3B><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/uannid.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Anni D</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(1/31/02 1:22:52 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm19.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1975.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Climbing + No Res = Useless skill</span><hr size=1> Get a grip.<br>
<br>
You want to sneak into their fort alone and have no risk?<br>
<br>
It is a risky deal. You have the chance to cause an enormous amount of disruption in there. It stands to reason that you do so at great risk to yourself.<br>
<br>
Come on people, stop thinking we are gods. We are just sneaks, nothing more. If the risk is too much for you, stand on the sidelines. I have no problem with going in myself. It is what I signed up for, and without the risk, I would not even bother.<br>
<br>
-Anni <p>A.K.A.
Moonflower
Nightshade/Seamstress
Hibernia-Guinivere</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2f2f4f><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/bthesafehouse.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=ebullition>Ebullition</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(1/31/02 2:12:00 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm19.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1975.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Climbing + No Res = Useless skill</span><hr size=1> Anni -<br>
<br>
What other class in a Keep take can't get a rez?<br>
<br>
You may like risk, but I don't call that risk, I call running back for 20 minutes so I can fight for 1 minute borring.  Plus, as a kobold, there are some keeps that I can NOT jump out of since I can't get over the walls.  Trying to climb that little climb spot in lag is near impossible.<br>
<br>
Also, now people just sit right next to climb spot and wack you while you are climbing.  They can hit you through the wall before you even get inside.<br>
<br>
Climb was a neat thing when we could get rez, but now it is really not very useful.  Yes you can do a suicide run, or maybe kill one person and get out alive.  But in truth Climb is about as useful as Detect Danger, Distraction and Safe Fall.  All of these &quot;skills&quot; have some use, but the uses are rare and really don't offer much utility.<br>
<br>
There needs to be at least 6 or 8 climb spots on every keep, every race regardless of size should be able to jump over the walls, and Milegates need climb spots.  Until we get more climb spots this &quot;skill&quot; is really not very useful, especially now when just about any class in the game can just lag right through the doors/walls.<br>
<br>
  <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#3B3B3B><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/unyvinyd.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Nyvinyd</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(1/31/02 2:12:26 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm19.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1975.topic&index=3>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Climbing + No Res = Useless skill</span><hr size=1> I started a Shadowblade because just like on EQ, I loved being able to dish out more than I can take.  It seems to work very well.  Over time I've found ways to kill things faster than a warrior, and if in group with a skald, damage buffs make me nigh-godlike to orange mobs.<br>
<br>
I really like my SB.  I just wish I had some damned spells.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> Edit: See my comments in your second post. - Tibis</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> <p><center><img src=http://www.rockapella.com/IMAGES/rocktype.gif></center></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/utibishatter.showPublicProfile?language=EN>TibisHatter</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/image/globalBlack.gif" BORDER=0> at: 1/31/02 3:44:08 am<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2f2f4f><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/uannid.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Anni D</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(1/31/02 2:58:14 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm19.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1975.topic&index=4>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Climbing + No Res = Useless skill</span><hr size=1> You should really pick one argument and stick with it. You bounce around little things like some crack crazed kangaroo.<br>
<br>
Shorten the edge mini walls for shorties to jump over. <br>
<br>
That is the only complaint that I can see that holds any merit.<br>
<br>
People can not run through the doors anymore, that was fixed in the patch.<br>
<br>
People are guarding the climb spots. <br>
<br>
Tough, what do you expect them to do? Roll out a red felt rope with a welcome sign?<br>
<br>
You confuse the ability to climb walls with a skill that says get anywhere you want with the greatest of ease.<br>
<br>
Taking a keep is meant to be somewhat difficult. Otherwise we would be to keep seiges what archers are to ganking people as they walk out of their realm keeps.<br>
<br>
If you don't want to risk having a 20 minute stroll, then by all means stay outside where it is safe and rez ready.<br>
<br>
If there is no risk, what meaning does victory really have?<br>
<br>
-Anni <p>A.K.A.
Moonflower
Nightshade/Seamstress
Hibernia-Guinivere</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#3B3B3B><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/unyvinyd.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Nyvinyd</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(1/31/02 3:12:54 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm19.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1975.topic&index=5>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www.jurassic5.com/images/index_logo.gif WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Climbing + No Res = Useless skill</span><hr size=1> Back in the day people used to pour burning oil on people who were climbing the castle walls, or just knock them down to their doom.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> Edit: Please keep in mind the forum signature rules - sig once per thread, and the combined size for signature pic and personal pic must be no more than 15k.  Thank you! - Tibis</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> <p></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/utibishatter.showPublicProfile?language=EN>TibisHatter</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/image/globalBlack.gif" BORDER=0> at: 1/31/02 3:46:46 am<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2f2f4f><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/bthesafehouse.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=majin>Majin</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(1/31/02 3:38:53 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm19.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1975.topic&index=6>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Climbing + No Res = Useless skill</span><hr size=1> No way to argue with Anni, did that already. No chance of understanding from her side =)<br>
<br>
Let it go <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#3B3B3B><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/bthesafehouse.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=back>Back</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(1/31/02 3:41:22 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm19.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1975.topic&index=7>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Climbing + No Res = Useless skill</span><hr size=1> Bah...it works just fine.  Yeah it sucks to get uncovered and killed on their side of the fort but tough. We took a keep this evening and it worked like this:<br>
hide + climb + poison (debuff and disease) target pesky caster on wall PA and hop back down (they wont follow you into a mass of trolls).  If you did not kill them then reapply poisons + stealth + climb back up and hit em again.  You are doing 2 things here.<br>
1) pesky caster is not nuking your door beaters and healers while he is resting, running or just plain scared to death you are gonna hit him again.<br>
2) pesky healers are busy healing or rezzing pesky caster and are not AE mezzing your door beaters or healers.<br>
And the added bonus of them healing at least twice before they figure out (or the caster tells) that he has been diseased and is wasting mana  <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
Then we got really smart and 4 SB's got together.  Each with a different poison on our weapon.  All attacked the same target and hopped back down.  We rallied through 4 healers and 2 casters, then took out their archers and boom the keep was ours again. (4 PA's in a row kills just about anything)<br>
<br>
Stop whining and use your brain!<br>
<br>
BTW there is a bug from the last patch that is allowing people to walk though walls and that damn point blank DD goes straight through the wall still too.  Guess that fix didnt work completely.  And BTW I am a Kobold and have no problems hoping the wall (not sure about Lurikeens).<br>
<br>
Back <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2f2f4f><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/uubergnome563.showPublicProfile?language=EN>ubergnome563</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(1/31/02 4:00:52 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm19.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1975.topic&index=8>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> .</span><hr size=1> we took a team of 4 40+ infiltrators into a siege merchant keep and cleared all of the archers (full spawn) + 1 defender tank before they got the second door (both level 1) half way down.  I tanked them being 48 at the time and brition (more hp).  Other rogues were 45, 40, and 42.  No deaths (closest i came is like 2% health, MANY of the archers were orange at 4<!--EZCODE EMOTICON START 8) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/glasses.gif ALT="8)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> , but did learn some interesting aggro bugs inside keeps in relation to archers,  it may even be possible to kill a keep lord with 12 assassins if the same bugs hold true for its aggro.<br>
<br>
Climb owns as long as you dont expect to climb over the wall with a cleric bot outside the walls making you invincible <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#3B3B3B><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/uvalarauco.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Valarauco</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(1/31/02 4:32:03 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm19.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1975.topic&index=9>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://home.attbi.com/~bdemong/valaface.gif WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: .</span><hr size=1> I had a very similar experience ubergnome.  Four 29-47 assassins slew the two PCs repairing the door (only defense) and all the parapet archers before the army at the gates took down the second door.  I've never had so much fun in a keep fight.<br>
<br>
My other &quot;very fun&quot; keep experiences have all been as a result of having Climb Walls.  It's great. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2f2f4f><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/uannid.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Anni D</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(1/31/02 5:33:07 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm19.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1975.topic&index=10>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: .</span><hr size=1> Thank you for the backup.<br>
<br>
I think it is an awesome ability. It doesnt turn you into a one person army, but with a few friends, it can be a force to be dealt with. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
-Anni <p>A.K.A.
Moonflower
Nightshade/Seamstress
